OL,3,CSpending abroad: What are the hidden
OL,4,Cfees and how can you avoid them?
OL,6,FMost ATMs in Greece require a fee
OL,7,Franging from two to four euros (#1.70-
OL,8,F#3.40), and retailers often prefer
OL,9,Fcustomers to pay using cash.
OL,11,FUnless you're using an Italian bank
OL,12,Fcard, ATM fees are commonly around one
OL,13,Fto five euros (#0.85-#4.26). Card
OL,14,Fpayments are commonly accepted but
OL,15,Fsome services such as buses may only
OL,16,Faccept cash.
