OL,3,CSpending abroad: What are the hidden
OL,4,Cfees and how can you avoid them?
OL,6,FOut-of-network transactions often
OL,7,Fincur fees from one dollar to more
OL,8,Fthan five dollars (#0.77- #3.87) in
OL,9,Fthe US, however some banks offer
OL,10,Frefunds for these fees. Although cash
OL,11,Fdoes remain the most popular choice
OL,12,Ffor transactions in the USA, card
OL,13,Fpayments are widely accepted.
OL,15,FIndependently owned ATMs often incur
OL,16,Ffees from between two and five
OL,17,FAustralian dollars (#1-#2.58). Card
OL,18,Fand contactless payments are the most
OL,19,Fpopular form of payment in Australia.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
